A "throne" made from various bones and... waste... likely gathered from all about these tunnels. But what is it doing here?

Value.value: These creatures clearly have no interest in constructing anything so the question is, what could -make- them construct this?
From what you've seen from the creatures that dwell here so far they have only two desires; eat and breed. So why would they construct a throne?
You are left wondering what could make these ravenous creatures stop to construct a throne; perhaps some greater denizen of whatever realm they spawned from waits below.

Filled with crabbed script that gradually becomes more and more erratic and rambling, this notebook tells the tale of the arcanist Thirurmorn of Kohlingen and his investigations of the Gibberling tunnels below the Amia Frontier. His writings mention purple 'chaos crystals', 'the Far Realm' and, cryptically, 'the master'. At irregular intervals the author suddenly interrupts his text with page after page of shaky handwriting, apparently transcriptions of the Gibberling shrieks and howls.

It is clear that this once proud and upstanding citizen of Kohlingen quickly degenerated into utter madness at the insistent whisperings of some unknown power.
<c  >**You feel a strange uneasiness as you enter this room, the scene before you certainly grisly and foreboding... but something more feels -wrong- about this place...**</c>
